result.execSummary:
The defendant Mohseen A Syed was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Mohseen A Syed in court with attorney James Gregory McCann.  John Daniel Flynn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2:
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.

AS TO COUNT 3: 
Pursuant to negotiations and upon motion of the State Count 3 is dismissed and read-in for sentencing. 

 SENTENCING PROCEEDED:
Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  

AS TO COUNT 1:
Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent with count 2 with credit for ZERO days served. 
Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 14 MONTHS concurrent with the following conditions:
- Serve 30 days in the House of Correction; STAYED pending review.
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety; random urine screens.
- Attend treatment and/or counseling as determined.
- No contact with victim.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- No contact with firearms.
- The court ordered defendant to pay the costs during the period of probation otherwise will result in a civil judgment. The court found that the defendant is indigent and imposed the DNA sample and the DV evaluation but waived the surcharges for them.
- Pay supervision fees.
